<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-24T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/1347.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-24T22:00:00+08:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1912—10 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Bankers to-day submitted plan sent from London for supervision and
                                control of loan expenditures, including foreign administration of
                                salt gabelle, to the Minister of Finance. The plan was emphatically
                                rejected. It is not anticipated that any adequate control can be
                                secured. Apparently groups will have to break off negotiations for a
                                while at least.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>